Package ohos.wearable.complication

Class Complication

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.wearable.complication.Complication

  • public class Complication
extends java.lang.Object
    Defines complication data types.

    Complications are components used to display data on the watch face. The type of data displayed can be a launcher icon, a long text string, simple data, ranged data, and list data.

    Since:
    5

      • TYPE_NO_DATA

        public static final int TYPE_NO_DATA
        Indicates a complication that displays no data. This type is applicable when no valid data can be displayed.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • TYPE_RANGED

        public static final int TYPE_RANGED
        Indicates a complication that displays ranged data.

        The watch face displays a template that may contain an icon, a title and ranged data, as defined in ComplicationTemplate. The ranged data includes maximum, minimum and current values, all of which are of the float type.

        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • TYPE_SIMPLE

        public static final int TYPE_SIMPLE
        Indicates a complication that displays simple data.

        The watch face displays a template that may contain an icon, a title and simple data (float or string), as defined in ComplicationTemplate.
